Job Scope:
Assistant for producing, complementing, and maintaining the Quality Management System to comply with ISO13485;
Participating in design control activities (including drafting design reviews, verification, and validation protocols and reports from time to time);
Participating in the risk analysis process, review of risk management documents, and tracking any pending issues or recommended actions of FMEAs;
Implementing and monitoring the effectiveness of the corrective and preventive actions (CAPA), ensuring proper documentation, timely execution, and verifying the completion/effectiveness of the CAPA activities;
Handle quality checking for the various products and incoming raw materials.
Perform regular quality inspections per established specifications and procedures (e.g. incoming, in-process, and final inspection);
Collaborate with team members to understand the procedure and product changes from time to time;
Support the R&D and production team for quality-related matters, such as raw material quality inspection, troubleshooting for the issues raised from the customer’s feedback, failure investigation of product, problem-solving, and root cause analysis during design and manufacturing;
Provide effective oversight of the execution of Quality Plans, Risk Management activities, and all design-related activities during the product lifecycle;
Perform the validation check based on usability, reliability, performance, supportability and manufacturability, and safety;
Responsible for performing regular inspection, and audit activities as needed, and ensuring quality requirement compliance;
Lab-related ad-hoc tasks may be assigned from time to time.
Requirement:
Degree in Chemical and Biological Engineering, Chemistry, Chemical Engineering, or Material Science Engineering or related major.
Preferred 1 year of experience in Quality related roles and involved in QMS system and certified as internal quality auditor; However, fresh graduates with Quality Roles during the internship experience are also welcome to apply;
Possess good interpersonal and multi-tasking skills;
Knowledge of ISO 13485 requirements is a plus point, but not necessary. Training will be provided;
Eager to learn and able to handle challenges, independent and meticulous;
Able to multi-task and work in a fast-paced environment;
Good documentation and organization skills;
Good communication skills;
Able to learn fast and adapt quickly to a new environment;
Being able to read and write in English and Mandarin is a plus point, but not compulsory.
Job type
Permanent/ Full time.

About the Company

N-Lab Technology Center Pte Ltd is a local company in Singapore since 2018. Through years of R&D studies in the In-Vitro Diagnostic (IVD) industries, we are proud to provide our customers with high-quality magnetic beads based on their requirements. We focus on two fields of research and experimental development: (1) on chemicals, such as magnetic beads with application in the In-Virto Diagnostics (IVD) field; and (2) on advanced materials in medical applications.
As the company expands, we need more talent like you, who have a strong interest in the medical-related company and are passionate about their roles. If you are interested in starting your career in the IVD industry-related field, understand how polymer science can lead to technology improvement, are passionate about research and development, eager to learn hands-on experiences and skill-building for your career path, then do not miss this opportunity!

